# openRS_ Release Checklist

Every time a new app version is released (versionName bump in `build.gradle.kts`), ALL of the following must be completed **before** committing and pushing:

## 1. CHANGELOG.md
- `android/CHANGELOG.md` — add a new `## [vX.Y.Z] — YYYY-MM-DD` section at the top
- Describe every fix and change under clear headings (`### Fixed`, `### Added`, `### Changed`)

## 2. Root README.md (single source of truth)
- **Root** `README.md` version badge: `https://img.shields.io/badge/version-X.Y.Z-blue`
- CAN ID table: reflect any ID additions/removals/corrections
- OBD polling table: reflect any new/removed PIDs or formula changes
- Feature descriptions: update if any features were added or removed
- Do NOT update `android/README.md` with shared content — it links to root

## 3. Browser Emulator

File: `android/browser-emulator/index.html`

This file mirrors the app UI. Every visible change to the app **must** be reflected in the emulator in the same commit/release. Check each category:

- **Version badge** — update `openRS_ vX.Y.Z` text in the `<div class="version-badge">` and `<div class="settings-version">`
- **Data cell labels** — if any `dc-label` text changed in the app (e.g. "FUEL RAIL" → "HP FUEL"), update it in the emulator
- **New widgets / rows** — if a new row was added to any tab (e.g. odometer row, new data cell), add matching HTML in the emulator
- **Removed widgets** — if something was removed from the app (e.g. gear display), remove it from the emulator too
- **MORE tab sections** — if a new section was added (e.g. "Module Status"), add it to the emulator; if a section heading changed, update it
- **Feature cards** — if a Features card was added, renamed, or its locked/unlocked state changed, reflect that in the emulator
- **TPMS decimal places** — `displayTire()` must use `.toFixed(1)` for PSI to match the app
- **Demo data** — simulated values should reflect real-world plausible readings
- **`toggleOdom()` or any new JS toggle** — if a new interactive element was added to the app, add matching JS in the emulator

## 4. Firmware (if firmware also changed)
- `firmware/CHANGELOG.md` must be updated
- Firmware version bumped in `focusrs.h` (`OPENRS_FW_VERSION`)
- `firmware/patches/apply_patches.py` — `OPENRS_FW_VERSION` must match `focusrs.h`
- **Binaries MUST be rebuilt from source**: `./build.sh --target usb` and/or `./build.sh --target pro`
  - Do NOT rename or copy a previous version's binary — this does nothing; the old code is still compiled in
  - `build.sh` generates `firmware/release/BUILD_MANIFEST_<target>.json` with SHA-256 hashes, git commit, and build timestamp
- **Run `./firmware/verify-release.sh`** before committing — it checks:
  - Every binary's SHA-256 matches the manifest
  - No binary is identical to a different version (catches copy/rename)
  - Manifest git commit matches HEAD
- Release binaries placed in `firmware/release/` (named `openrs-fw-usb_vXXX.bin`, `openrs-fw-pro_vXXX.bin`)
- Commit the manifest alongside the binaries — CI will reject stale binaries on push to main
- Firmware releases are **per-device** — each device gets its own GitHub release (see below)

## 5. Pre-release (staging → testing)
When pushing significant changes to `staging` that aren't ready for `main`:

### Tagging convention
- Android: `android-vX.Y.Z-rc.N`
- Firmware USB: `fw-usb-vX.Y-rc.N`
- Firmware Pro: `fw-pro-vX.Y-rc.N`

### Steps
- Tag: `git tag <tag> staging && git push origin <tag>`
- Create: `gh release create <tag> --prerelease --target staging --title "<title>" --notes "<notes>"`
- Attach: unsigned/debug APKs or firmware `.bin` files for testers
- Pre-releases show on the Releases page with a badge but do NOT replace the "Latest" stable release
- When ready to ship: promote to stable release (see step 6)

### Firmware: separate releases per device
- Each device target gets its own pre-release (e.g. `fw-usb-v1.4-rc.1` and `fw-pro-v1.4-rc.1`)
- Attach only that device's flash files (bootloader, partition-table, ota_data, app binary)
- Pro releases are only created after the build is verified on actual hardware

## 6. GitHub Release (stable)

### Android app
- Merge `staging` → `main`, then tag: `git tag android-vX.Y.Z && git push origin android-vX.Y.Z`
- Create release: `gh release create android-vX.Y.Z --title "openRS_ vX.Y.Z — <short description>" --latest --notes "<notes>"`
- **APK is attached automatically** by the `publish-release` CI job when the `android-v*` tag is pushed
- The CI job builds a signed release APK using GitHub Secrets (`KEYSTORE_BASE64`, `KEYSTORE_PASSWORD`, `KEY_ALIAS`, `KEY_PASSWORD`) — ensure these are configured in the repo settings
- Release notes must summarise every user-visible change
- Verify the APK appears on the release page after CI completes

### Firmware (per device)
- Run `./firmware/verify-release.sh` — must pass before creating the release
- Tag: `git tag fw-usb-vX.Y && git push origin fw-usb-vX.Y` (and/or `fw-pro-vX.Y`)
- Create: `gh release create fw-usb-vX.Y firmware/release/bootloader_usb.bin firmware/release/openrs-fw-usb_vXXX.bin firmware/release/ota_data_initial_usb.bin firmware/release/partition-table_usb.bin --title "openrs-fw USB vX.Y" --notes "<notes>"` (use `_pro` suffixes for Pro releases)
- USB and Pro get separate releases — versions may diverge over time
- Reference firmware releases in the app release notes if both ship together

## 7. GitHub Issues Milestone
- Check the milestone for this release (e.g. `v2.3.0 — Tech Debt + Polish`)
- Verify all implemented issues have staging comments per `issue-lifecycle.mdc` (use `refs #N` in commits, NOT `fixes #N`)
- On stable release (staging merged to main): batch-close all shipped issues with `gh issue close <N> --comment "Shipped in <version>."`
- Move any unfinished issues to the next milestone

## Quick Verification
Before creating the release, ask:
- [ ] Does `versionName` in `build.gradle.kts` match the CHANGELOG entry?
- [ ] Does the **root** README version badge match?
- [ ] Does the emulator match the app UI?
- [ ] Are any removed widgets also removed from the emulator?
- [ ] Are any formula changes reflected in the emulator and README?
- [ ] Is the APK attached to the GitHub release?
- [ ] (Firmware) Does `./firmware/verify-release.sh` pass?
- [ ] (Firmware) Is `BUILD_MANIFEST_<target>.json` committed alongside the binaries?
- [ ] Do all addressed issues have staging comments per `issue-lifecycle.mdc`?
